    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-06-14T16:40:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-06-14T16:40:00-05:00" n="782"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d782">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">839.00/2399: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in the Dominican Republic</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Russell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santo Domingo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-06-14T17:00:00-04:40">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 14, 1921—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 15—3:54 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>20. Proclamation issued today and was received with a hot blast of protest from
                    the press advising the people not to accept it as this would imply sanction of
                    past wrongs, and it has been suggested that the people refuse to take part in
                    the elections.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Russell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
